,Not Recommended,235360,9824758,"Posted: 15 April, 2014",all,John,"I'm starting to see why the metascore is quite low. Despite it being low, the game has it's good moments. At start, I loved the game, I still play it from time to time. The idea of having different towers and magic abilities, which you can customize, is great. Towers and magic are aquired through cards. When it comes to customization, it means you can customize what towers you take with you and you can reinforce these towers with fusing different cards. The crafting isn't hard to grasp, you either improve a card or evolve a card. Evovling meaning, ie. a tower can be upgraded to the next level, meaning you can in-game upgrade the tower. There are 3 tiers when it comes to evolution, default, upgraded and max evolution.It is a great game, but playing and progressing requires you to play same map, again and again. At some point through the main story, you will get the next map which you can finish, if you can't you have three different challenges from where you get more cards, easy, medium and hard. These kind becomes your bread and butter, grinding these challenges for more cards, so that you can progress and make better towers.At some point, you will notice that there are very little variety to the game. Challenge maps will be recycled, which imo, isn't too bad. But you will see same enemies over and over again, in different colors. The challenge will be different, even though you have the same enemy, but the only difference is that the monster can tank more damage.If you don't mind the grinding and similiarites through the game, I would recommend this game. Good game with an good idea, but somewhat poorly designed. I think the metascore is true and correct, but that doesn't mean the game is bad or not fun. I would recommend watching some gameplay vids, before considering buying the game. Still a decent tower defense game."
,Not Recommended,235360,8637899,"Posted: 9 January, 2014",all,[TI] Ajf151,"While this game is fun, the original developers have all left the company that is responsible for the upkeep of the game.  Achievements do not work and there is no guarantee they will start working again.  There is no developer support.  For that reason, and until the game is fixed, I do not recommend buying it.  Sorry to everyone that bought it in the holiday/seasonal sales; it's apparently been broken for months.  I didn't notice until a few days ago.Gameplay wise, the TD mechanics are solid and the card system makes for an interesting twist on figuring out a playstyle that works for you with the cards you have.  There are, however, a few missions along the way that simply cannot be beaten unless you and your cards are leveled up enough.  You simply won't have enough damage to outpace healing, for example, or you won't be able to kill the flyers and the ground units with the resources available unless both sets of towers are strong enough to hit the benchmark of cost efficiency necessary to kill stuff before it gets to the end of the maze.  That, to me, is bad design.  It isn't enough to prevent me to urge anyone not to buy it, but you should be aware of the possibility of needing to grind to get strong enough to beat certain levels.  Other than that, I recommend it."
