,Recommended,235360,8242072,"Posted: 23 December, 2013",all,バゼーア,"Prime World Defenders is the best tower defense game on PC. It combines a classic TD-game with a trading card game with many features, looks very nice and you can choose many different play styles, all what you need in a good TD-game. But you need to grind a little bit to get these cards or you buy booster-packs from the ingame-store, don’t worry, it’s not pay-2-win. If you are not sure, try the demo version of this game or the free version on iOS or Android.StoryThis game has not really a story with a meaning. It’s completely irrelevant and can be ignored, how all TD-games oyu play this for the gameplay and not for a interesting story.GameplayLike a standard TD-game you do exactly the same in Prime World Defenders. You choose a level and build your towers to defense your base against the enemies. There are fixed points to build the towers and some of them have special effects like more damage or areas that increase the range or the attack speed. There are also magic spells including freeze, fire, thunderbolt etc.To be able to upgrade your towers you must collect trading cards and to get them, you need to finish the levels or collect silver and buy some booster-packs from the store. Every Tower or magic spell is a card and you need two of them to combine them to upgrade them ingame. To level up your cards you can use very card, depending on how rare the cards are you get more or less experience points.After finishing all levels in the normal mode you unlock the hard mode. To beat this and maybe to collect all the achievements, you have to grind a long time.GraphicPrime World Defenders looks nice for a TD-Game. The game has a comic style with nice visual effects and is very clear, also the User Interface. The UI is very big because it’s just a port from mobile devices.Prime World Defenders is the best tower defense game on the PC. It looks very nice and clear, it’s not pay-2-win and you have a lot to do if you want. It is also the best TD-game on the iPad. If you have both, I recommend you to choose the tablet version. Unfortunately you can’t synchronize your progress between mobile version and Steam. That’s the only negative point here."
