,Recommended,235360,10211469,"Posted: 23 May, 2014",all,Foghorn Dickhorn,"Decent tower defense game, but completely abandoned by the developers.  As a result, many steam achievements won't unlock (although they do unlock in game, they just have difficulty  syncing up), and this is likely to never be fixed.  End game grinding is a bit tedious, as you're stuck with one of two options to obtain rare towers -- endless survival grinding for a chance at a rare card, and then a chance to pick that card from a set, or logging in every day to get a ""daily bonus"" which has the possibility of being a rare card.It has a lot of card fusing and upgrading, which is kind of a side point to the main game, but it allows you to individually customize your tower set to only upgrade what you use, which is pretty nice.  The unfortunate part of this is the lack of a reliable method to get said towers.  As far as gameplay goes, it's a pretty well done TD, although your ability to path monsters via tower placement is virtually non existant, and your towers are confined to rails along the sides for the most part.  This is it's only real drawback, in that it's more like Kingdom Rush than Defense Grid.All in all, decent game, but it unfortunately will never be great with a developer team giving it any post-release attention.  8/10.  Good for probably 40ish hours, with some additional hours if you enjoy the grind to max out your towers."
